AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - SOUTH AFRICA (03): (NORTHERN CAPE) DOMESTIC, OIE
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 11 Sep 2019
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2019; 32(37) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31717


African swine fever, South Africa
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Sep 2019 from Dr. Bothle Michael Modisane, chief director, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Sep 2019
Report date: 11 Sep 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 11 Sep 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 26 Aug 2019
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever [ASF] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (ASF_NCP_2019_001): ASF_NCP_2019_001, Siyancuma, Northern Cape province
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 85 / 57 / 57 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 67.06 / 67.06 / 100 / 67.06
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Not epidemiologically linked to South Africa's other ASF event. Outside South Africa's ASF control zone. Coordinates modified to protect confidentiality as required by South African legislation.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; quarantine; zoning; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Agricultural Research Council - Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute, Transboundary Animal Diseases Programme (ARC-OVI TADP) (OIE reference laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 11 Sep 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In addition to this latest African swine fever (ASF) event, since April 2019 to date (12 Sep 2019), South Africa continues to have 2 active events. The status of each of these events is as follows:

Event 1 started on 3 Apr 2019; one outbreak was reported. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30106.

Event 2 started on 15 Apr 2019; 16 outbreaks were reported. The event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30214.

These 17 outbreaks are located outside of South Africa's ASF control zone, affecting the provinces of North West, Mpumalanga, Gauteng, and Free State. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Northern Cape region, South Africa: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6669709,12176]
